02 mouse-tRNA Age modeling

Richard J. Acton

2020-01-06

1 Introduction

Using mouse RRBS sequencing data from [1] GSE80672 and mouse tRNA data from GtRNAdb [2] to examine changes in tRNA gene DNAm with Age.

2 Set-up

2.1 Libs

suppressPackageStartupMessages({
    library(GenomicRanges)
    library(BSgenome.Mmusculus.UCSC.mm10)
    library(TxDb.Mmusculus.UCSC.mm10.knownGene)
    library(tidyverse)
    library(plyranges)
    library(patchwork)
})
if(!dir.exists("graphics")) {
    dir.create("graphics", showWarnings = FALSE, recursive = TRUE)
}

4 Preprocessing

4.1 tRNA data

removing tRx regions

mousetRNAsSet <- 
mousetRNAs %>%
    as_tibble() %>%
    extract(
        name, into = c("tRNA", "aa", "anticodon", "f", "s"),
        regex = "(\\w+)-(\\w+)-(\\w+)-(\\w+)-(\\w+)",
        remove = FALSE
    ) %>% 
    filter(tRNA == "tRNA") %>%
    dplyr::select(-blocks) %>%
    as_granges()
ntRNAs <- length(mousetRNAsSet)

sws <- 0.05 / length(mousetRNAsSet)

6 Age modeling

6.1 by tRNA

quickAgeModels <- 
tRNAAndMethDF %>%
    dplyr::filter(cov >= 50) %>%
    group_by(name) %>%
    nest() %>%
    mutate(model = map(data, ~lm(age ~ meth, data = .x))) %>%
    mutate(tidy = map(model, broom::tidy)) %>%
    unnest(cols = c(tidy)) %>%
    mutate(
        term = case_when(
            term == "(Intercept)" ~ "intercept",
            term == "meth" ~ "slope",
        )
    ) %>%
    dplyr::select(-std.error, -statistic, -p.value) %>%
    spread(term,estimate) %>%
    mutate(glance = map(model, broom::glance)) %>%
    unnest(cols = c(glance)) %>%
    arrange(p.value)
essentially perfect fit: summary may be unreliableessentially perfect fit: summary may be unreliableessentially perfect fit: summary may be unreliableessentially perfect fit: summary may be unreliableessentially perfect fit: summary may be unreliableessentially perfect fit: summary may be unreliable
quickAgeModelssws <- 
quickAgeModels %>% 
    dplyr::select(-data, -model) %>%
    filter(p.value < sws)
quickAgeModelssws
quickAgeModels %>%
    group_by(sign(slope)) %>%
    dplyr::summarise(n = dplyr::n())
quickAgeModels %>%
    filter(p.value < 0.05) %>%
    group_by(sign(slope)) %>%
    dplyr::summarise(n = dplyr::n())

7.3 by CpG

CpGsig <- 0.05 / nCpGsAvail
CpGsig
[1] 0.0001146789
quickAgeModelsCpG <- 
tRNAAndMethDF %>%
    dplyr::filter(cov >= 50) %>%
    group_by(name,start) %>%
    dplyr::filter(dplyr::n() > 10) %>%
    nest() %>%
    mutate(model = map(data, ~lm(age ~ meth, data = .x))) %>%
    mutate(tidy = map(model, broom::tidy)) %>%
    unnest(cols = c(tidy)) %>%
    mutate(
        term = case_when(
            term == "(Intercept)" ~ "intercept",
            term == "meth" ~ "slope",
        )
    ) %>%
    dplyr::select(-std.error, -statistic, -p.value) %>%
    spread(term,estimate) %>%
    mutate(glance = map(model, broom::glance)) %>%
    unnest(cols = c(glance)) %>%
    arrange(p.value)

quickAgeModelsCpGsws <- 
quickAgeModelsCpG %>% 
    dplyr::select(-data, -model) %>%
    filter(p.value < CpGsig) ### !!! acctual not total number of sites
quickAgeModelsCpGsws
quickAgeModelsCpG %>%
    group_by(sign(slope)) %>%
    dplyr::summarise(n = dplyr::n())
quickAgeModelsCpG %>%
    filter(p.value < 0.05) %>%
    group_by(sign(slope)) %>%
    dplyr::summarise(n = dplyr::n())
quickAgeModelsCpG %>%
    dplyr::select(-data, -model) %>%
    filter(p.value < 0.05)
byCpGplot <- function(df,modres) {
    
    addmod <- function(start) {
        sapply(start, function(srt){
            row <- modres %>% filter(start == srt)
            paste0(
                #sprintf("R² = %.2f,\n p = %.2e\n", row$r.squared, row$p.value),
                "CpG: \n", format(as.numeric(srt), big.mark = ",")
            )
        })
    }
    
    df %>%
    ggplot(.,aes(age, meth)) + 
        geom_point(size = 0.8) +
        geom_smooth(aes(colour = `Significance`), method = "lm") + 
        facet_grid(
            paste0(
                gsub(name, pattern = "tRNA-", replacement = ""),
                " (", tools::toTitleCase(as.character(seqnames)), ")"
            ) ~ start,
            labeller = labeller(start = addmod),
            scales = "free"
        ) + 
        scale_colour_manual(values = c("darkblue","orange","red")) +
        scale_fill_discrete(drop=FALSE) + 
        theme_bw() + 
        theme(legend.position = "bottom") + 
        lims(y = c(0,85))+
        labs(
            x = "Age /months",
            y = "methylation /%"
        )
}
CpGPlots <- 
tRNAAndMethDF %>%
    dplyr::filter(cov >= 50) %>%
    dplyr::filter(name %in% quickAgeModelsCpGsws$name) %>%
    left_join(quickAgeModelsCpG,by = c("name","start")) %>%
    mutate(
        `Significance` = case_when(
            p.value < CpGsig ~ sprintf("p < %.3e",CpGsig),
            p.value < 0.05 ~ "p < 0.05",
            TRUE ~ "NS"
        )
    ) %>%
    group_by(name) %>%
    dplyr::filter(dplyr::n() > 10) %>%
    do(
        plots = byCpGplot(., quickAgeModelsCpG)
    ) #%>%
    #pull(plots)

#CpGPlots %>% pull(plots)
CpGPlotComb <- 
    {CpGPlots$plots[[1]] + theme(legend.position = "none")} /
    {CpGPlots$plots[[3]] + theme(legend.position = "none")} /
    CpGPlots$plots[[2]]
CpGPlotComb

ggsave(
    CpGPlotComb,
    filename = "graphics/CpGPlotComb.png",
    width = 9,
    height = 7
)
